cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.MM, cs.IT

The paper discusses the use of deep learning for denoising arterial spin labeling (ASL) cerebral blood flow (CBF) images. This involves image processing and machine learning, which are both covered by the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. The incorporation of prior knowledge about ASL MRI also involves information theory (cs.IT) and potentially multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
